title: General Partner (financial)
description: General partners are the full, but not necessarily equal, partners in an investment fund. They will participate in most funding and investment decisions, and will often specialize in a certain category or market segment. In some partnerships, partners are compensated equally while in others they 'eat what they kill', that is, they reap most of their compensation from the investments they brought to the fund.
